#: ../../M/MIPS.rst:12
msgid ""
"A measure of computing speed; formally, ‘Million Instructions Per Second’ "
"(that's :math:`10^{6}` per second, not :math:`2^{20}`\\! ); often rendered "
"by hackers as ‘Meaningless Indication of Processor Speed’ or in other "
"unflattering ways, such as ‘Meaningless Information Provided by Salesmen’. "
"This joke expresses an attitude nearly universal among hackers about the "
"value of most :ref:`benchmark` claims, said attitude being one of the great "
"cultural divides between hackers and :ref:`marketroid`\\s (see also "
":ref:`BogoMIPS`\\). The singular is sometimes ‘1 MIP’ even though this is "
"clearly etymologically wrong. See also :ref:`KIPS` and :ref:`GIPS`\\."
msgstr ""
"計算速度の尺度。正式には‘Million Instructions Per Second(毎秒百万命令)’(これは毎秒\\ "
":math:`10^{6}`\\ であって\\ :math:`2^{20}`\\ ではない!)。ハッカーはしばしば‘Meaningless "
"Indication of Processor Speed(無意味なプロセッサ速度表示)’や、‘Meaningless Information "
"Provided by Salesmen(営業マンが提供する無意味な情報)’などの誉められない形で表す。この冗談は、ほとんどの\\ "
":ref:`benchmark`\\ の主張の価値についてハッカーの間でほぼ普遍的な態度を表しており、その態度はハッカーと\\ "
":ref:`marketroid`\\ の間の大きな文化的隔たりの一つである(\\ :ref:`BogoMIPS`\\ も参照)。単数形は時に‘1 "
"MIP’とされるが、これは明らかに語源的に間違っている。\\ :ref:`KIPS`\\ や\\ :ref:`GIPS`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../M/MIPS.rst:19
msgid ""
"Computers, especially large computers, considered abstractly as sources of "
":ref:`computron`\\s. \"This is just a workstation; the heavy MIPS are hidden"
" in the basement.\""
msgstr ""
"コンピュータ、特に大型コンピュータを、抽象的に\\ :ref:`computron`\\ "
"の供給源と見なしたもの。「これはただのワークステーションだ。重いMIPSは地下に隠してある」。"

#: ../../M/MIPS.rst:23
msgid ""
"The corporate name of a particular RISC-chip company, later acquired by SGI."
msgstr "ある特定のRISCチップ企業の社名。のちにSGIに買収された。"

#: ../../M/MIPS.rst:26
msgid ""
"Acronym for ‘Meaningless Information per Second’ (a joke, prob. : from sense"
" 1)."
msgstr "‘Meaningless Information per Second(毎秒無意味な情報)’の頭字語(冗談。おそらく語義1から)。"
